        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down. Bromley Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Sunday</date>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>My dear Hooker</p>
<p>What a splendid, magnificent letter from Asa Gray!<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I should out of pure vanity rather like to keep first sheet, so do not throw it away.—<ref target="#foot.f3"/> It is rich about Agassiz.</p>
<p>I mean to come to London on Tuesday evening for the vain purpose of consulting a new Doctor for my stomach;<ref target="#foot.f4"/> &amp; for the Club on Thursday, where, if I can possibly, attend, I very much hope to see you.<ref target="#foot.f5"/> What a time it is since I have seen you my dear old friend, &amp; such kind &amp; generous sympathy you have shown me.—</p>
<p>God Bless you | Yours affect | C. Darwin</p>
<p>I tried to come up last Thursday to dine at Athenæum with you Naturalists, but failed.</p>
<p>I hope Lady Hooker goes on favourably.—<ref target="#foot.f6"/></p>
<p>Is there a cool-greenhouse Goodenia, so that I could get a plant &amp; examine the process of impregnation?<ref target="#foot.f7"/></p>
<p>A capital clear article in todays Gardener Ch. I suppose by you.—<ref target="#foot.f8"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.2 sheet] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘note’</note>
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n2">7.1 A capital … you.—-] <hi rend="italic">pencil</hi></note>
